Subject Classification¶
The BASE index supports the Dewey Decimal Classification (DDC) for subject categorization. The assignment
of Dewey classes to documents is established in two ways:
manually for contents from repositories that use the DDC.
automatically through machine learning-based document categorization.
Depending on their origin, the Dewey numbers are either stored in the field classcode
(for manually assigned numbers) or autoclasscode (for automatically assigned numbers).
The field deweyfull can be used for querying both manually and automatically
classified documents.
Example Queries:
Filter for mathematical documents (manually and automatically classified):
http://oai.base-search.net/oai?verb=ListRecords&metadataPrefix=base_dc&set=deweyfull:51*
Filter for manually classified mathematical documents:
http://oai.base-search.net/oai?verb=ListRecords&metadataPrefix=base_dc&set=classcode:51*
Filter for automatically classified mathematical documents:
http://oai.base-search.net/oai?verb=ListRecords&metadataPrefix=base_dc&set=autoclasscode:51*
Encoding in the base_dc format:
<base_dc:classcode type="ddc">510</base_dc:classcode>
Conversely, if the class was assigned automatically, it would look like this:
<base_dc:autoclasscode type="ddc">510</base_dc:autoclasscode>
Open Access Status¶
BASE indexes the Open Access status of full text documents where this information is available.
The status is stored numerically encoded in the field oa.
